                                        "},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"We are given "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"32 | 10000a + 1000b + 100c + 10d + e"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". The factors of "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"10"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" are "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2 * 5"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":", and since all of the terms are divisible by "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" except for the last one, we look to make the last one a multiple of 5. This can be done by adding "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"64e"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" (since e is an integer, it still satisfies the divisibility condition). Since "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"32"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" are coprime, we can divide the right hand side by 5 while still preserving the divisibility condition, resulting in "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2000a + 200b + 20c + 2d + 13e"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". So now the answer is either "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":". "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" doesn't work if d is odd, e.g. abcde = 22656, as the resulting sum would be odd. Thus, "},{"type":"katex","content":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}],"attrs":{"inline":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is minimized as possible."}]},{"type":"text","text":"



